  <h2>Installing AEM Forms on JEE</h2> 
  <p>Perform the following steps to install and configure AEM Forms on JEE:</p> 
  <ol> 
   <li><p>Download the AEM 6.4 Forms on JEE installer from the <a href="http://licensing.adobe.com/">Adobe Licensing Website (LWS)</a>. You require a valid Maintenance &amp; Support contract to download the installer.</p>  </li> 
   <li><p>Read the <a href="../../forms/using/AEM-forms-JEE-supported-platforms.md" target="_blank">AEM Forms on JEE Supported Platforms document</a> and ensure that have the software, hardware, operating systems, application server, databases, JDKs, and other infrastructure ready to install AEM Forms on JEE.</p> </li> 
   <li><p>(Non-Turnkey installs only) Read the <a href="http://www.adobe.com/go/learn_aemforms_prepareInstallsingle_64">Preparing to install AEM Forms single server</a> or <a href="http://www.adobe.com/go/learn_aemforms_prepareInstallcluster_64">Preparing to install AEM Forms server cluster</a> and ready your environment to install and configure AEM Forms on JEE.</p> </li> 
   <li><p>Depending on your environment and application server, choose one of the following documents and follow the instructions to complete the installation</p> 
    <ul> 
     <li><a href="http://www.adobe.com/go/learn_aemforms_installTurnkey_64">Installing and deploying AEM Forms on JEE using JBoss turnkey</a></li> 
     <li><a href="http://www.adobe.com/go/learn_aemforms_installJBoss_64">Installing and deploying AEM Forms on JEE for JBoss</a></li> 
     <li><a href="http://www.adobe.com/go/learn_aemforms_installWebLogic_64">Installing and deploying AEM Forms on JEE for WebLogic</a></li> 
     <li><a href="http://www.adobe.com/go/learn_aemforms_installWebSphere_64">Installing and deploying AEM Forms on JEE for WebSphere</a></li> 
     <li><a href="http://www.adobe.com/go/learn_aemforms_clusterJBoss_64">Configuring AEM Forms on JEE on JBoss cluster</a></li> 
     <li><a href="http://www.adobe.com/go/learn_aemforms_clusterWebLogic_64">Configuring AEM Forms on JEE on WebLogic cluster</a></li> 
     <li><a href="http://www.adobe.com/go/learn_aemforms_clusterWebSphere_64">Configuring AEM Forms on JEE on WebSphere cluster</a></li> 
    </ul> 
    <note> 
     <p>On the Module selection screen of AEM Forms on JEE configuration manager, select the Document Security option. The Document Security option does not require any other module to be selected.</p> 
    </note></li>  
  </ol> 
